      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "HERE'S HERBIE (5) is a newcomer to the Bond yard from NZ where he was last seen winning at Motukarara three-and-a-half months ago. He looks well placed to kick off in WA with a win. BEATITLIKEBECA (1) led from this draw when he won nicely two back at Pinjarra then stuck on well for second here last time, beaten 2 metres. Could give a sight from the ace draw. MY COPY NZ (2) draws well and could be close to a win after placing in his last three outings, the latest coming in a G3 where he recovered after galloping from the standing start. OPAL HUNTER (3) will be fitter for the fresh effort from a wider barrier. Should not have any excuses from the favourable draw.",
